    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="487"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d487">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Edward M. House Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName type="to"
                            >Wilson</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-10">November 10,
                            1918</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. In view of the enormous claims which the French and Belgian Governments will
                    make on Germany I think we should get our engineers to make an approximate
                    estimate for our guidance. If you approve I can have this begun at once.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward House</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
